        BRIEF SUMMARY OF GIT WORKFLOW

1 clone repo (git clone (url)

2 cd into cloned repo 

3 check current branch create your safe branch “git checkout -b branch name”
-creates new branch
-moves in it along content of main

4 Make any change 

5 git status to see change in local working directory

6 git add “filename” …NOW IN STAGE AREA

7 git commit -m “ Message”. …NOW IN REPO

8 git push -u origin clone.me ..creates a new remote branch clone_practice an push there even though it will still push to origin from which we cloned from 


STEP 2 — Merge Into Main (Professional Way)
You DO NOT push directly to main.
Instead:
1️⃣ Go to GitHub 2️⃣ Click Compare & Pull Request 3️⃣ Base branch: main 4️⃣ Compare branch: clone.me 5️⃣ Create Pull Request 6️⃣ Merge Pull Request

1. After this stage in the clone process go back to terminal and checkout to your master or main branch 

2. In master run git pull (you want your github updated branch content matching  local master branch or production branch) 

